<refsect1 xml:id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para>This procedure returns the current value of the <emphasis remap='B'>tk_strictMotif</emphasis>
variable in the interpreter associated with <emphasis remap='I'>tkwin</emphasis>'s application.
The value is returned as an integer that is either 0 or 1.
1 means that strict Motif compliance has been requested, so anything
that is not part of the Motif specification should be avoided.
0 means that
<quote>Motif-like</quote>
is good enough, and extra features are welcome.</para>

<para>This procedure uses a link to the Tcl variable to provide much
faster access to the variable's value than could be had by calling
<emphasis remap='B'>Tcl_GetVar</emphasis>.</para>

</refsect1>

